### THE CHAPTER OF EL KÂUTHAR.

### (CVIII. Mecca.)

IN the name of the merciful and compassionate God.  
Verily, we have given thee El KâuTHar <span
id="fr_504"></span>[3](#fn_504.md); <span id="page_343">p. 343</span>  
So pray to thy Lord and slaughter (victims).  
Verily, he who hates thee shall be childless <span
id="fr_505"></span>[1](#fn_505.md).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Footnotes

<span id="fn_504"></span>[342:3](108.htm#fr_504.md) The word signifies
'abundance.' It is also the name of a river in Paradise.

<span id="fn_505"></span>[343:1](108.htm#fr_505.md) This is directed
against Âs ibn Wail, who, when Mohammed's son El Qâsim died, called him
abtar, which means 'docktailed,' i.e. childless.

